<title>USA: CEZ files with US SEC for note offering.</title>
<headline>CEZ files with US SEC for note offering.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-07-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>CEZ Finance B.V, a unit of CEZ a.s., the largest electricity company in the Czech Republic, filed Tuesday with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission to register an offering of up to $200 million in guaranteed notes due 2007.</p>
<p>Underwriters for the offering are J.P. Morgan &amp; Co, Merrill Lynch &amp; Co and Salomon Brothers Inc.</p>
<p>Proceeds from the sale will be used to make capital expenditures, to refinance short-term borrowings and for other general corporate needs.</p>
